      "writtenOn": "2017-07-28T13:15:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m borrowing \"with\" from the python context manager convention, as it runs the passed-in function within the context of the \"try to modify the CL but don\u0027t error out if it was closed\".  \"Modify\" because the passed-in function modifies the CL.  Happy to rename if you can think of something better.  Could be as simple as \"modify\" I guess.",
